A classic Aston Martin once owned by Spartacus star Peter Ustinov is set to fetch more than £ 1million at auction .
The actor bought the Aston Martin DB4 Cabriolet in 1962 , shortly after winning a Best Supporting Actor Oscar for his role as Batiatus in Spartacus .
It was one of the most luxurious cars of its day when the average house price in Britain was just £ 2,500 .
The car is expected to sell for around £ 1 million next month .